Both worklist views are wired through `WorklistRows`. Two genuinely new things stand out from the just-landed sort work:

1. **`aria-sort` is inert.** Commit `0593d98` set `aria-sort` on plain `<span>`s inside a role-less grid `<div>` (`worklist-rows.tsx:120`). Without `role="columnheader"`/`role="row"`, ARIA ignores `aria-sort` — so the accessibility signal that phase added doesn't actually reach assistive tech. The progress note even flagged there's no real `<th>` here.

2. **Dead static header in `plan-rows.tsx`.** `PlanRows`' `showHeader` defaults `true` (lines 37–49), but the only caller, `WorklistRows`, always passes `showHeader={false}`. So that non-sortable header — the pre-sort version the worklist header superseded — never renders in the app.

